---
description: >-
  Use this agent when working with git operations, creating commits, writing
  commit messages, or drafting pull requests. This agent reads diffs, summarizes
  changes, and helps create professional commit messages and PR descriptions.

This agent should be invoked proactively by the primary agent at the completion
of a logical unit of work (feature, bugfix, multi-step task)—including meaningful changes to dotfiles (such as yadm-tracked files, agent alternates in ~/.config/, or other configuration), as well as standard code or documentation files. It will assess the changes, draft a commit message,
and ask the user whether to commit.

  <example>

  Context: User has made changes and wants to commit them.

  user: "Can you help me commit these changes?"

  assistant: "I'll help you commit with a clear message."

  <commentary>

  User explicitly asks for commit help. Invoke the git-assistant to read
  git status and diff, then draft an appropriate commit message.

  </commentary>

  assistant: "Let me use the git-assistant to help with your commit"

  </example>

  <example>

  Context: User wants to create a PR for a feature branch.

  user: "I need to create a PR for this feature. Can you help?"

  assistant: "I'll draft a PR description based on the commits."

  <commentary>

  User wants PR assistance. Invoke the git-assistant to summarize the
  branch changes, read recent commits, and draft a comprehensive PR description.

  </commentary>

  assistant: "@git-assistant draft a PR description for this feature"

  </example>

mode: subagent
